WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:10.301 --> 00:00:14.389 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Otome: A maiden
smelling sweet as a flower,

00:00:14.472 --> 00:00:17.392 position:50% align:center
a single bud blooming
in a tranquil garden,

00:00:17.475 --> 00:00:20.061 position:50% align:center
pure and dignified.

00:00:20.145 --> 00:00:23.148 position:50% align:center
Too shy to ever speak
of love or romance,

00:00:23.231 --> 00:00:28.236 position:50% align:center
she dares not allow herself
to even dream of a kiss.

00:00:28.319 --> 00:00:31.489 position:50% align:center
Even so, she blooms again today.

00:00:31.573 --> 00:00:36.161 position:50% align:center
Seeking, ever pursuing
happiness beyond the stars.

00:02:07.585 --> 00:02:11.506 position:50% align:center
Huh?! Kotori and
Shiratori are twins?

00:02:11.589 --> 00:02:13.550 position:50% align:center
Your reaction is
quite entertaining.

00:02:13.633 --> 00:02:15.552 position:50% align:center
We're sorry to
drop in like this,

00:02:15.635 --> 00:02:18.972 position:50% align:center
but, um, I need to ask
a favor from Yuzuki.

00:02:19.055 --> 00:02:19.681 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI]
Hm?

00:02:19.764 --> 00:02:20.974 position:50% align:center
A favor from me?

00:02:21.057 --> 00:02:23.143 position:50% align:center
Yes! I hope this is okay.

00:02:23.226 --> 00:02:24.728 position:50% align:center
I don't know who
would know better.

00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:26.396 position:50% align:center
Will you teach me about love?

00:02:26.479 --> 00:02:29.566 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI]
Huh?! Are you serious?

00:02:29.649 --> 00:02:31.776 position:50% align:center
You see, there's
this girls' magazine

00:02:31.860 --> 00:02:34.195 position:50% align:center
that I've been writing
a column for.

00:02:34.279 --> 00:02:35.697 position:50% align:center
Oh, I know!

00:02:35.780 --> 00:02:37.991 position:50% align:center
It's this one. <i>Kotori's Book</i>
<i>of Advice</i> , right?

00:02:38.074 --> 00:02:40.577 position:50% align:center
It's so amazing.
I read it all the time.

00:02:40.660 --> 00:02:43.830 position:50% align:center
Oh, good! That makes
it a little easier.

00:02:43.913 --> 00:02:45.707 position:50% align:center
First, I've heard of this.

00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:47.792 position:50% align:center
Lately it seems I've been
getting more questions

00:02:47.876 --> 00:02:50.628 position:50% align:center
about that subject than usual.

00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:55.467 position:50% align:center
Love and relationships.

00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:57.677 position:50% align:center
I thought I'd write a song
to support and celebrate

00:02:57.761 --> 00:03:00.638 position:50% align:center
all of the young women going
through those intense emotions.

00:03:00.722 --> 00:03:02.849 position:50% align:center
Except I've never been in love.

00:03:02.932 --> 00:03:04.976 position:50% align:center
Wouldn't that make writing
the song a bit tricky?

00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:08.021 position:50% align:center
Exactly! So you can
see the problem!

00:03:08.104 --> 00:03:10.857 position:50% align:center
You see, after Hakaru
told me your love story,

00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:13.234 position:50% align:center
I knew that's what I
wanted to write about.

00:03:13.318 --> 00:03:15.737 position:50% align:center
So that's why I
came to meet you.

00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:18.907 position:50% align:center
What? Oh my goodness!
What do you mean "love story"?

00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:20.700 position:50% align:center
What did you tell her?

00:03:20.784 --> 00:03:22.118 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU whistles]

00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:24.454 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO growls]

00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:25.789 position:50% align:center
I'm begging you.

00:03:25.872 --> 00:03:27.207 position:50% align:center
I would love to fly to the side

00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:30.502 position:50% align:center
of every heartbroken
girl who contacts me.

00:03:30.585 --> 00:03:33.338 position:50% align:center
And unfortunately, I can't.

00:03:33.421 --> 00:03:37.008 position:50% align:center
But my music can comfort
them wherever they are!

00:03:37.092 --> 00:03:39.886 position:50% align:center
I can transform myself
into a song that speaks

00:03:39.969 --> 00:03:41.429 position:50% align:center
to what they're going through,

00:03:41.513 --> 00:03:44.933 position:50% align:center
and give them the understanding
and encouragement they need!

00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:46.351 position:50% align:center
Music is magic.

00:03:46.434 --> 00:03:49.354 position:50% align:center
I can be a friend to
a lonely lovesick girl,

00:03:49.437 --> 00:03:52.232 position:50% align:center
I can make someone who's
crying smile again,

00:03:52.315 --> 00:03:55.944 position:50% align:center
or I can empower someone
with low self-esteem.

00:03:56.027 --> 00:04:00.031 position:50% align:center
Interesting. I actually do
get what you're saying.

00:04:00.115 --> 00:04:02.575 position:50% align:center
Singing is something
I love, too!

00:04:02.659 --> 00:04:04.119 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Mh-hm! Mh-hm!

00:04:04.202 --> 00:04:07.747 position:50% align:center
I've always been amazed by the
healing power of good music!

00:04:07.831 --> 00:04:10.458 position:50% align:center
You're so adorable, Kotori!

00:04:14.421 --> 00:04:15.839 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:21.302 position:50% align:center
Here, I don't know if we'll
be much help musically,

00:04:21.386 --> 00:04:24.431 position:50% align:center
but you're welcome to use
this room for composing.

00:04:24.514 --> 00:04:26.182 position:50% align:center
Wow. You mean you'll
let me stay here

00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:28.309 position:50% align:center
until my song is
completely finished?

00:04:28.393 --> 00:04:29.686 position:50% align:center
Absolutely!

00:04:29.769 --> 00:04:31.563 position:50% align:center
Wait here, I'll get your futon.

00:04:31.646 --> 00:04:33.440 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much!

00:04:33.523 --> 00:04:35.734 position:50% align:center
What great news! Well done!

00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:38.278 position:50% align:center
Thanks! I'm gonna work hard!

00:04:38.361 --> 00:04:42.240 position:50% align:center
I think I came up with
the first few bars already.

00:04:42.323 --> 00:04:45.952 position:50% align:center
[humming]

00:04:46.036 --> 00:04:47.954 position:50% align:center
Not much, but you like it?

00:04:48.038 --> 00:04:49.748 position:50% align:center
Uh.

00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:53.126 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I think it sounds great.

00:04:54.461 --> 00:04:57.714 position:50% align:center
Well then,
I guess I better go.

00:04:57.797 --> 00:05:00.258 position:50% align:center
Just like he always does.

00:05:02.552 --> 00:05:04.095 position:50% align:center
That's better, now let's go--

00:05:04.179 --> 00:05:04.846 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Huh?

00:05:04.929 --> 00:05:06.306 position:50% align:center
[BOTH yelp]

00:05:13.605 --> 00:05:15.065 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI chuckles]

00:05:16.107 --> 00:05:17.317 position:50% align:center
Don't pay attention to me.

00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:20.070 position:50% align:center
Just be yourselves.
Pretend I'm not even here!

00:05:20.153 --> 00:05:22.405 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO, YUZUKI]
That's impossible!

00:05:22.489 --> 00:05:25.241 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Hi, Mister Tamahiko!

00:05:25.325 --> 00:05:27.911 position:50% align:center
Tamahiko! You there, Yuzu?

00:05:27.994 --> 00:05:30.205 position:50% align:center
I brought you two
some yummy goodies!

00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:31.790 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI laughs]

00:05:31.873 --> 00:05:33.500 position:50% align:center
Look at all these
adorable children!

00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:35.377 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:37.170 position:50% align:center
Uh, isn't that...?

00:05:37.253 --> 00:05:39.756 position:50% align:center
It's Kotori!

00:05:39.839 --> 00:05:42.342 position:50% align:center
Aw, c'mon. Your eyes are
just playing tricks on ya!

00:05:42.425 --> 00:05:43.760 position:50% align:center
There's no way!

00:05:43.843 --> 00:05:48.348 position:50% align:center
Oh, it's true!
Hello, it's me, Kotori!

00:05:48.431 --> 00:05:51.017 position:50% align:center
[CHILDREN]
Huh?!

00:05:51.101 --> 00:05:54.604 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO] All right,
shall we begin today's lesson?

00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:58.400 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI laughing]

00:05:58.483 --> 00:06:00.193 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Well, hello, there!

00:06:00.276 --> 00:06:04.030 position:50% align:center
Oh, great. So much
for all my plans.

00:06:04.114 --> 00:06:05.490 position:50% align:center
Class! Listen!

00:06:05.573 --> 00:06:08.326 position:50% align:center
This is our guest teacher
for today, Miss Kotori!

00:06:08.410 --> 00:06:11.830 position:50% align:center
[CHILDREN]
Huh? Yay!

00:06:11.913 --> 00:06:14.582 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] Okay! I wanna
hear everyone sing!

00:06:14.666 --> 00:06:18.420 position:50% align:center
First let's all take
a deep breath. And go!

00:06:18.503 --> 00:06:22.257 position:50% align:center
[ALL] ♪ Dear little
redbird in the sky ♪

00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:25.844 position:50% align:center
♪ How'd your feathers
get so bright ♪

00:06:25.927 --> 00:06:31.683 position:50% align:center
♪ Strawberry fruit
that grows nearby ♪

00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:33.435 position:50% align:center
Yuzu, too?

00:06:33.518 --> 00:06:34.477 position:50% align:center
[RYO laughs]

00:06:34.561 --> 00:06:37.147 position:50% align:center
How fun! I know
this song, too! Yay!

00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:39.399 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
♪ ...get so bright ♪

00:06:39.482 --> 00:06:42.068 position:50% align:center
Everyone's welcome to join!

00:06:44.487 --> 00:06:48.116 position:50% align:center
[ALL] ♪ Dear little
bluebird in the sky ♪

00:06:48.199 --> 00:06:51.911 position:50% align:center
♪ How'd your feathers
get so bright ♪

00:06:51.995 --> 00:06:53.955 position:50% align:center
♪ Blueberry fruit... ♪

00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:56.958 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT H] I got caught by
Ol' Gramophone yesterday.

00:06:57.042 --> 00:06:58.043 position:50% align:center
Gramo-who?

00:06:58.126 --> 00:06:59.961 position:50% align:center
Uh, the literature teacher.

00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:02.088 position:50% align:center
He does not know
how to stop talking!

00:07:02.172 --> 00:07:05.633 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS, HAKURA chuckling]

00:07:05.717 --> 00:07:08.386 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT H]
Ugh, damn it all!

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:11.139 position:50% align:center
I can't believe I left
my pencil case at home.

00:07:11.222 --> 00:07:13.266 position:50% align:center
Along with my brain.

00:07:13.350 --> 00:07:17.437 position:50% align:center
Aw. If only I had a spare
pencil on me, but I do not.

00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.230 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT A]
Neither do I.

00:07:20.982 --> 00:07:24.778 position:50% align:center
Does anyone else have
a pencil he could borrow?

00:07:28.365 --> 00:07:30.700 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO]
Uh. I, um--

00:07:31.659 --> 00:07:35.455 position:50% align:center
Here. Take it.
I mean, if you want to!

00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:40.710 position:50% align:center
Wow! That's amazing!
Thank you so much!

00:07:42.128 --> 00:07:44.589 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU] I've got something
delicious to share.

00:07:44.673 --> 00:07:47.008 position:50% align:center
Take a look at what
Shima let me borrow!

00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:48.426 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS gasp]

00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:50.470 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT H]
Whoa! <i>Juicy Night-Time Club</i> ?

00:07:50.553 --> 00:07:52.013 position:50% align:center
[yelps]

00:07:52.097 --> 00:07:53.807 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT A] No way!
Is that the latest issue?

00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:57.018 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT I]
Shima is the man!

00:07:57.102 --> 00:08:00.814 position:50% align:center
Shiratori, where
did you get that?

00:08:04.067 --> 00:08:05.360 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU]
I feel like I've already gotten

00:08:05.443 --> 00:08:06.820 position:50% align:center
used to this school.

00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:08.530 position:50% align:center
I think that's just
because your sister

00:08:08.613 --> 00:08:10.532 position:50% align:center
is famous and also cute.

00:08:10.615 --> 00:08:14.077 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't go that far.
I mean, I'm cute, too!

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:16.538 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:08:16.621 --> 00:08:20.125 position:50% align:center
Speaking of, do you know
how Kotori's been doing?

00:08:20.208 --> 00:08:23.503 position:50% align:center
She's been getting along great
with Yuzu and the others.

00:08:23.586 --> 00:08:26.297 position:50% align:center
And of course,
the kids are overjoyed.

00:08:28.383 --> 00:08:30.552 position:50% align:center
Such garbage.

00:08:30.635 --> 00:08:34.889 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO] Although she's having
a hard time writing her song.

00:08:34.973 --> 00:08:36.099 position:50% align:center
Now that I think about it,

00:08:36.182 --> 00:08:38.268 position:50% align:center
you haven't been by
to see her, have you?

00:08:38.351 --> 00:08:39.811 position:50% align:center
That's no good.

00:08:39.894 --> 00:08:42.731 position:50% align:center
Why don't you stop by after
class? Yuzu would be thrilled.

00:08:42.814 --> 00:08:44.649 position:50% align:center
Not to mention Kotori.

00:08:44.733 --> 00:08:49.195 position:50% align:center
No thanks. I appreciate
the offer, though.

00:08:49.279 --> 00:08:52.157 position:50% align:center
Please say hi to
my sister for me.

00:08:52.240 --> 00:08:53.742 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO]
Huh.

00:08:54.826 --> 00:08:56.828 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI] I brought you
a snack if you're hungry.

00:08:56.911 --> 00:08:58.288 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Aw, thanks!

00:08:58.371 --> 00:09:01.583 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI] Have some!
They're called madeleines, and--

00:09:04.127 --> 00:09:07.630 position:50% align:center
Um, are you gonna be all right?

00:09:07.714 --> 00:09:10.383 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
It's no use, I've hit a wall.

00:09:10.467 --> 00:09:13.803 position:50% align:center
I know! Tell me the story
of how the two of you met.

00:09:13.887 --> 00:09:14.804 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI]
Huh?

00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:17.390 position:50% align:center
Yuzu! Please, tell me!

00:09:17.474 --> 00:09:20.518 position:50% align:center
Well, if you really
want to know.

00:09:22.437 --> 00:09:24.522 position:50% align:center
I came here when I agreed
that I would take care of

00:09:24.606 --> 00:09:27.025 position:50% align:center
and one day marry
Mister Tamahiko.

00:09:27.108 --> 00:09:29.319 position:50% align:center
I admit I was worried
about meeting him,

00:09:29.402 --> 00:09:34.074 position:50% align:center
but once I did, that's when
everything started to change.

00:09:34.157 --> 00:09:39.120 position:50% align:center
I thought, "It's gonna be okay.
There's something about him.

00:09:39.204 --> 00:09:42.332 position:50% align:center
I know in my heart he'll
grow to cherish me."

00:09:42.415 --> 00:09:44.250 position:50% align:center
I was so bewildered
by the feelings

00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:46.628 position:50% align:center
that were bubbling
up inside of me.

00:09:46.711 --> 00:09:49.881 position:50% align:center
There was a tightness in
my chest I'd never felt.

00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:51.633 position:50% align:center
It was kinda like
the panic you get

00:09:51.716 --> 00:09:54.386 position:50% align:center
when you're not sure about
a decision you made.

00:09:54.469 --> 00:09:59.140 position:50% align:center
But, um, without... the fear.

00:09:59.224 --> 00:10:02.185 position:50% align:center
When did it begin? I'm not sure.

00:10:02.268 --> 00:10:04.062 position:50% align:center
It happened every
time I saw him.

00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:06.523 position:50% align:center
Whenever I saw his integrity
or awkward kindness,

00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:09.234 position:50% align:center
I'd get butterflies.

00:10:09.317 --> 00:10:11.611 position:50% align:center
Sometimes it became unbearable.

00:10:11.695 --> 00:10:14.114 position:50% align:center
I couldn't control
the feelings inside.

00:10:14.197 --> 00:10:17.450 position:50% align:center
I didn't trust my heart
and that scared me.

00:10:17.534 --> 00:10:19.285 position:50% align:center
I thought, what if--

00:10:19.369 --> 00:10:22.247 position:50% align:center
I know it's crazy--
but what if--?

00:10:22.330 --> 00:10:25.208 position:50% align:center
Was it love? Tell me!

00:10:26.292 --> 00:10:29.004 position:50% align:center
Does it feel like you can't ever
stop thinking about him?

00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:31.089 position:50% align:center
You're amazed at how much
fun you have together?

00:10:31.172 --> 00:10:34.801 position:50% align:center
And you're happiest when you're
just imagining being with him?

00:10:36.261 --> 00:10:38.096 position:50% align:center
That doesn't mean
it's always easy.

00:10:38.179 --> 00:10:40.682 position:50% align:center
When things get hard,
you feel uncertain.

00:10:40.765 --> 00:10:45.061 position:50% align:center
And yet, you hold on
because you love him.

00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:48.648 position:50% align:center
I do. That's exactly right.

00:10:48.732 --> 00:10:50.150 position:50% align:center
Well, I'll be.

00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:53.403 position:50% align:center
That's the same way I feel
about creating my music!

00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:54.612 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:56.489 position:50% align:center
I finally understand it!

00:10:56.573 --> 00:10:58.700 position:50% align:center
Love doesn't have to be
about another person.

00:10:58.783 --> 00:11:01.995 position:50% align:center
I feel the way you
do about my music.

00:11:02.078 --> 00:11:04.497 position:50% align:center
Wow! There's a great
song in there!

00:11:04.581 --> 00:11:07.542 position:50% align:center
Thank you! You're a good friend!

00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:11.212 position:50% align:center
Oh, my. A maiden in love is
truly magnificent to behold!

00:11:11.296 --> 00:11:13.465 position:50% align:center
I've learned so much
from you today, Yuzu!

00:11:13.548 --> 00:11:17.802 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI] I didn't do anything!
We were just talking!

00:11:17.886 --> 00:11:20.180 position:50% align:center
But I'm looking forward to
hearing your love song.

00:11:20.263 --> 00:11:22.807 position:50% align:center
I just know it's
gonna be perfect.

00:11:22.891 --> 00:11:24.059 position:50% align:center
Thanks!

00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:26.353 position:50% align:center
No one's more passionate
about music than you!

00:11:26.436 --> 00:11:28.229 position:50% align:center
Every song you write
comes from your heart,

00:11:28.313 --> 00:11:30.732 position:50% align:center
that's what makes
them so wonderful.

00:11:30.815 --> 00:11:33.151 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
I wouldn't say "no one."

00:11:33.234 --> 00:11:34.652 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:34.736 --> 00:11:37.197 position:50% align:center
Hakaru's the one who fell
in love with music first,

00:11:37.280 --> 00:11:40.617 position:50% align:center
so he's got more experience
with it than I do.

00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:42.160 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:53.838 --> 00:11:56.091 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI]
How was your day at school?

00:11:56.174 --> 00:11:59.094 position:50% align:center
Uh, it was fine.

00:11:59.177 --> 00:12:01.012 position:50% align:center
Shiratori and I did
a little group reading

00:12:01.096 --> 00:12:03.640 position:50% align:center
together with friends.

00:12:03.723 --> 00:12:05.475 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI]
Oh! That sounds like fun!

00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:08.436 position:50% align:center
You really love
books, don't you?

00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:10.480 position:50% align:center
Uh, yeah.

00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:14.484 position:50% align:center
But, anyway, I've actually had
something else on my mind.

00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.569 position:50% align:center
It feels like Shiratori
might be avoiding

00:12:16.653 --> 00:12:19.447 position:50% align:center
talking to Kotori
for some reason.

00:12:19.531 --> 00:12:22.909 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I've noticed
that, too, I'm afraid.

00:12:22.992 --> 00:12:24.411 position:50% align:center
I don't know if
this even matters,

00:12:24.494 --> 00:12:26.746 position:50% align:center
but Kotori told me it was Hakaru

00:12:26.830 --> 00:12:28.581 position:50% align:center
who fell in love
with music first,

00:12:28.665 --> 00:12:30.834 position:50% align:center
back when they were little.

00:12:30.917 --> 00:12:34.546 position:50% align:center
Interesting. Hmm...

00:12:38.967 --> 00:12:43.054 position:50% align:center
Wow, so fancy!
Another luxurious lunch!

00:12:43.138 --> 00:12:44.889 position:50% align:center
I'll just help myself, thanks.

00:12:44.973 --> 00:12:46.474 position:50% align:center
Wha--?!

00:12:50.145 --> 00:12:53.440 position:50% align:center
Delish! Yuzu's a great cook!

00:12:53.523 --> 00:12:57.402 position:50% align:center
Hm? Here, you can have
some of mine if you want.

00:12:57.485 --> 00:12:58.862 position:50% align:center
I'm okay.

00:12:58.945 --> 00:13:01.406 position:50% align:center
But I was hoping to talk to
you about something else.

00:13:01.489 --> 00:13:03.158 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU]
Hm? About what?

00:13:03.241 --> 00:13:05.076 position:50% align:center
Do you want me to get you
the special supplement

00:13:05.160 --> 00:13:06.828 position:50% align:center
from the <i>Juicy Night-Time Club</i> ?

00:13:06.911 --> 00:13:08.246 position:50% align:center
No thanks!

00:13:08.329 --> 00:13:10.582 position:50% align:center
But, um, I was wondering,

00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:14.169 position:50% align:center
did you and Kotori have
some kind of falling out?

00:13:14.252 --> 00:13:15.545 position:50% align:center
Uh.

00:13:20.425 --> 00:13:21.926 position:50% align:center
No, not really.

00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:25.680 position:50% align:center
But I can tell you're gonna need
the full story to understand.

00:13:28.475 --> 00:13:32.479 position:50% align:center
You see, it wasn't just Kotori.
I got into music first.

00:13:32.562 --> 00:13:33.855 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:13:33.938 --> 00:13:39.986 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU] ♪ Alas, my love,
you do me wrong ♪

00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:46.326 position:50% align:center
♪ To cast me off
discourteously... ♪

00:13:46.409 --> 00:13:47.702 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU]
Soon enough,

00:13:47.786 --> 00:13:52.040 position:50% align:center
Kotori was singing right
along with me every time.

00:13:52.123 --> 00:13:55.835 position:50% align:center
But then, one day,
I got very sick.

00:13:55.919 --> 00:13:59.005 position:50% align:center
Recovering took all
the energy I had.

00:13:59.089 --> 00:14:02.300 position:50% align:center
There was no time
left for music.

00:14:02.384 --> 00:14:06.137 position:50% align:center
Here, Kotori. I want you
to have this. It's yours.

00:14:06.221 --> 00:14:07.138 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Huh?

00:14:07.222 --> 00:14:09.933 position:50% align:center
I won't be able to
play it anymore.

00:14:10.016 --> 00:14:12.560 position:50% align:center
But you can keep the music
alive for both of us.

00:14:12.644 --> 00:14:14.604 position:50% align:center
What are you talking about?

00:14:14.688 --> 00:14:16.523 position:50% align:center
Please take it!

00:14:16.606 --> 00:14:18.483 position:50% align:center
I want us to play together!

00:14:18.566 --> 00:14:21.403 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna practice every
day till you're better!

00:14:21.486 --> 00:14:26.074 position:50% align:center
Please! Just get better!
Please, Hakaru!

00:14:29.327 --> 00:14:31.371 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU]
My recovery took forever!

00:14:31.454 --> 00:14:33.665 position:50% align:center
Seven long years to be exact.

00:14:33.748 --> 00:14:36.334 position:50% align:center
The doctor said it
was a miracle.

00:14:36.418 --> 00:14:37.711 position:50% align:center
And before I knew it,

00:14:37.794 --> 00:14:40.797 position:50% align:center
Kotori launched her professional
career as a singer,

00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:43.550 position:50% align:center
and a popular one, at that.

00:14:43.633 --> 00:14:46.803 position:50% align:center
I didn't forget, Hakaru.
You made me a promise.

00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:50.306 position:50% align:center
You said we'd play together
when you got better.

00:14:52.809 --> 00:14:55.562 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU] I'd been fighting
my illness all that time.

00:14:55.645 --> 00:14:57.939 position:50% align:center
My body was worn out.

00:14:59.441 --> 00:15:01.609 position:50% align:center
Trying to match Kotori's
level at this point

00:15:01.693 --> 00:15:02.944 position:50% align:center
would be exhausting.

00:15:03.028 --> 00:15:04.946 position:50% align:center
There's no way.

00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:09.784 position:50% align:center
Guess it's finished.

00:15:13.079 --> 00:15:15.040 position:50% align:center
I'm the worst. I know.

00:15:15.123 --> 00:15:18.752 position:50% align:center
Me and my stupid
inferiority complex.

00:15:19.711 --> 00:15:23.298 position:50% align:center
Trust me, I know
exactly how you feel.

00:15:24.299 --> 00:15:27.135 position:50% align:center
After what happened to
my hand in that accident,

00:15:27.218 --> 00:15:30.638 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't even allow myself
to imagine a future.

00:15:30.722 --> 00:15:34.934 position:50% align:center
I woke up depressed every day.
All I wanted was to end it all.

00:15:35.018 --> 00:15:36.644 position:50% align:center
What was the point?

00:15:36.728 --> 00:15:41.566 position:50% align:center
But then Yuzu came and being
with her made me realize

00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:43.818 position:50% align:center
I wasn't giving myself a chance.

00:15:43.902 --> 00:15:46.112 position:50% align:center
I felt useless without my hand.

00:15:46.196 --> 00:15:47.822 position:50% align:center
I was denying my
new circumstance

00:15:47.906 --> 00:15:49.449 position:50% align:center
instead of adapting,

00:15:49.532 --> 00:15:53.161 position:50% align:center
which closed my heart to
anyone who tried to get in.

00:15:53.244 --> 00:15:55.163 position:50% align:center
[whimpers]

00:15:56.414 --> 00:15:58.750 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO]
Yuzu never gave up.

00:15:58.833 --> 00:16:01.586 position:50% align:center
She was the one
to unlock my heart.

00:16:07.425 --> 00:16:08.677 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:16:08.760 --> 00:16:11.888 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO] She inspired me
to face forward again.

00:16:17.310 --> 00:16:20.522 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO]
To finally take that first step.

00:16:22.857 --> 00:16:24.984 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO]
Now my world is expanding,

00:16:25.068 --> 00:16:28.071 position:50% align:center
with more and more
irreplaceable people.

00:16:28.154 --> 00:16:31.408 position:50% align:center
Bit by bit. Step by step.

00:16:32.951 --> 00:16:34.452 position:50% align:center
That includes you.

00:16:34.536 --> 00:16:37.288 position:50% align:center
You're one of the irreplaceable
people I have in my life now.

00:16:37.372 --> 00:16:38.331 position:50% align:center
Huh?!

00:16:38.415 --> 00:16:39.582 position:50% align:center
Uh! What?

00:16:39.666 --> 00:16:42.627 position:50% align:center
Ignore me. I don't know
what I'm saying!

00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:45.380 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry. I shouldn't
bother you with this.

00:16:45.463 --> 00:16:47.590 position:50% align:center
These are my own issues. Ugh.

00:16:47.674 --> 00:16:50.593 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU]
Thank you, you're amazing.

00:16:50.677 --> 00:16:54.180 position:50% align:center
I'm lucky to have such
good friends in my life.

00:16:54.264 --> 00:16:59.394 position:50% align:center
But I wonder, could Kotori be
waiting for me to figure it out?

00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:02.105 position:50% align:center
To open my heart again?

00:17:23.293 --> 00:17:25.754 position:50% align:center
[FUTOSHI]
Gather 'round, all and sundry!

00:17:25.837 --> 00:17:27.839 position:50% align:center
If you don't have somewhere
to be right now,

00:17:27.922 --> 00:17:30.175 position:50% align:center
take a moment to check this out!

00:17:30.258 --> 00:17:32.969 position:50% align:center
[MITSUKO] Kotori Shiratori is
about to debut a brand-new,

00:17:33.053 --> 00:17:35.096 position:50% align:center
piping-hot song on this stage!

00:17:35.180 --> 00:17:37.682 position:50% align:center
You don't want to miss it!

00:17:37.766 --> 00:17:39.225 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Come, all and sundry!

00:17:39.309 --> 00:17:42.979 position:50% align:center
Take a moment to enjoy
what you're about to see!

00:17:47.859 --> 00:17:50.028 position:50% align:center
Okay, here we go.

00:17:54.324 --> 00:17:55.825 position:50% align:center
But listen up, folks!

00:17:55.909 --> 00:17:57.452 position:50% align:center
We have a last-minute
performance to share

00:17:57.535 --> 00:18:00.538 position:50% align:center
before we go, so yay!

00:18:00.622 --> 00:18:02.123 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU]
Pardon me!

00:18:02.207 --> 00:18:05.710 position:50% align:center
Would it be all right to sing
one song before Kotori performs?

00:18:09.964 --> 00:18:11.966 position:50% align:center
What are you doing?

00:18:14.427 --> 00:18:16.304 position:50% align:center
This is "Bird on
a Moonlit Night."

00:18:16.388 --> 00:18:18.640 position:50% align:center
I hope you enjoy it.

00:18:21.518 --> 00:18:24.229 position:50% align:center
[HAKARU]
♪ There was a little bird ♪

00:18:24.312 --> 00:18:28.900 position:50% align:center
♪ as brokenhearted
as could be ♪

00:18:28.983 --> 00:18:36.032 position:50% align:center
♪ Treebound and warbling out
a melancholy melody ♪

00:18:36.116 --> 00:18:43.915 position:50% align:center
♪ Lost in the shadows with
the moonlight soft and low ♪

00:18:43.998 --> 00:18:47.669 position:50% align:center
♪ His teardrops fell
