00:20:32.857 --> 00:20:37.153 position:50% align:center
♪ As they float and play,
they're dancing light and free ♪

00:20:37.237 --> 00:20:41.241 position:50% align:center
♪ Petals blow away and
flutter to and fro ♪

00:20:41.324 --> 00:20:45.078 position:50% align:center
♪ Before they find
their way back home ♪

00:20:45.161 --> 00:20:49.416 position:50% align:center
♪ You hold it in your hands,
the passion in my heart ♪

00:20:49.499 --> 00:20:52.377 position:50% align:center
♪ For each and every
blossom is a prayer ♪

00:20:52.460 --> 00:20:54.629 position:50% align:center
♪ that we'll never be apart ♪

00:20:54.713 --> 00:20:58.967 position:50% align:center
♪ A bouquet unfurled
from the stars above ♪

00:20:59.050 --> 00:21:02.554 position:50% align:center
♪ That's the gift that
I'd give the world ♪

00:21:02.637 --> 00:21:04.931 position:50% align:center
♪ A rainbow song of love ♪

00:21:05.015 --> 00:21:06.516 position:50% align:center
What a great song.

00:21:06.599 --> 00:21:09.060 position:50% align:center
I agree.

00:21:09.144 --> 00:21:12.397 position:50% align:center
So, um, can I tell
you something?

00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:14.232 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO]
HM?

00:21:14.315 --> 00:21:15.316 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:21:15.400 --> 00:21:17.027 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI]
Hurry up and say it.

00:21:17.110 --> 00:21:22.240 position:50% align:center
"I think I-I might actually..."
Why can't I just spit it out?

00:21:22.323 --> 00:21:23.742 position:50% align:center
I, uh--

00:21:23.825 --> 00:21:24.701 position:50% align:center
What's wrong?

00:21:24.784 --> 00:21:25.702 position:50% align:center
Oh! Nothing!

00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:27.120 position:50% align:center
I was just thinking
about bicycles

00:21:27.203 --> 00:21:29.956 position:50% align:center
and how fun they are to ride--
not that I would know.

00:21:30.040 --> 00:21:32.375 position:50% align:center
Um, I was wondering
if you weren't busy,

00:21:32.459 --> 00:21:34.669 position:50% align:center
maybe you could teach
me how to ride one.

00:21:34.753 --> 00:21:36.338 position:50% align:center
That way I could go
with you everywhere

00:21:36.421 --> 00:21:39.632 position:50% align:center
and neither one of us
would have to be alone.

00:21:39.716 --> 00:21:43.053 position:50% align:center
Oh, well, no need for that.

00:21:43.136 --> 00:21:44.429 position:50% align:center
Honestly.

00:21:44.512 --> 00:21:46.723 position:50% align:center
I don't see why I can't take
you everywhere with me--

00:21:46.806 --> 00:21:48.516 position:50% align:center
just like this.

00:21:49.642 --> 00:21:50.894 position:50% align:center
From now on?

00:21:50.977 --> 00:21:52.228 position:50% align:center
[TAMAHIKO]
Yes.

00:21:52.312 --> 00:21:53.313 position:50% align:center
For always?

00:21:53.396 --> 00:21:56.191 position:50% align:center
Yeah, for always.

00:21:56.274 --> 00:22:01.196 position:50% align:center
All right! By your
side, for always.

00:23:38.752 --> 00:23:41.921 position:50% align:center
[YUZUKI] I'm going to Tokyo
to see my dear friend Midori.

00:23:42.005 --> 00:23:43.548 position:50% align:center
I haven't seen her in so long

00:23:43.631 --> 00:23:45.800 position:50% align:center
and I'm really looking
forward to it,

00:23:45.884 --> 00:23:49.012 position:50% align:center
but even though we'll only
be apart for a short while,

00:23:49.095 --> 00:23:52.140 position:50% align:center
I'm already missing
Mister Tamahiko.